{"article_id":"RcFv8EhO68S1R8eR","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In the final jobs report prior to the election , the Bureau of Labor Statistics has announced","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that unemployment crept up in October to 7.9 percent ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"as 170,000 nonfarm payroll jobs were added .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The broader `` U-6 '' unemployment statistic is 14.6 percent","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"( up a hair from 14.5 six months ago ) .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"August and September 's numbers were both revised upward ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"which is a positive sign .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"As Jim Pethokoukis notes ,","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"average monthly job growth in 2012 has been nearly identical to the sub-par numbers of 2011 ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"and hourly wages remain stagnant at best .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"The `` worst recovery since the Great Depression '' continues .","depth":4},{"id":11,"text":"Politically speaking ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"both sides will point to the figures","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that boost their chances ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"and the mixed news will certainly allow for that sort of jockeying .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Democrats will correctly say","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that the jobs added number was better","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"than expected ;","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Republicans will correctly argue","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"that job creation has been languishing ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and that the overall rate is again headed in the wrong direction .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"These facts remain :","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"Roughly 23 million Americans are out of work ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"have given up looking for work ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"or are under-employed .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Median household take-home pay has fallen by nearly $ 4,300 annually","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"since this president took office .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"And","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"upon passing the $ 825 Billion `` stimulus '' package ,","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"the administration confidently projected","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"that unemployment would be approximately 5.2 percent by now .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Instead , we 're stuck near or above eight percent for the 45th consecutive month .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Forward ?","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"The labor force participation rate , a key metric","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that measures those working and looking for jobs ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"edged higher to 63.8 percent","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"after wallowing around 31-year lows for the past several months .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"It 's still right there .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Former CBO director Douglas Holtz-Eakin offers a balanced assessment of today 's report :","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"- Job creation in August and September was revised up by a total of 84,000 jobs .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"- Job creation was more broadly spread than in previous months , with increases in both the goods- and services-producing sectors .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"- The labor force grew by 578,000","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"and the participation rate rebounded by 0.2 percent to 63.8 percent .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"However , the report was not unambiguous good news ,","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"as the foundations of income growth weakened :","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"- The average weekly earnings and index of weekly hours showed sharp declines .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"- The Hispanic unemployment rate mirrored the overall rate ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"rising from 9.9 to 10.0 .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"There will be celebration in some quarters over the top line job growth ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"but this is a triumph of diminished expectations .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"The report is a solid base hit","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"- not a home run -","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"in a game","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"where the U.S. is over 20 million runs behind .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"The Romney campaign will certainly use these new numbers","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"to emphasize their central theme :","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"That America needs a real , robust recovery","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"-- not one","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"that limps along in fits and starts .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"UPDATE II -","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Romney expresses dismay at our economy 's `` virtual standstill ''","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"( via his campaign ) :","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"\" Today ' s increase in the unemployment rate is a sad reminder","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"that the economy is at a virtual standstill .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"The jobless rate is higher","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"than it was","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"when President Obama took office ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"and there are still 23 million Americans","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"struggling for work .","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"On Tuesday , America will make a choice between stagnation and prosperity .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"For four years , President Obama ' s policies have crushed America ' s middle class .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"For four years , President Obama has told us","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"that things are getting better","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"and that we ' re making progress .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"For too many American families , those words ring hollow .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"We can do better .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"We can have real economic growth ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"create millions of good-paying jobs ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"and give middle-class families the security and opportunity","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"they deserve .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"When I ' m president ,","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"I ' m going to make real changes","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"that lead to a real recovery ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"so that the next four years are better than the last . \"","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"Black/African American unemployment rate jumps from 13.4 to 14.3 ,","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"Hispanic unemployment rate rises from 9.9 to 10.0 .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"- Zeke Miller","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"( @ ZekeJMiller )","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"November 2 , 2012","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"UPDATE IV -","depth":2},{"id":90,"text":"Be sure to review this summary infographic from American Commitment .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":181,"left":179,"right":180,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":101,"right":178,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":101,"left":97,"right":100,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":93,"right":96,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":0,"right":92,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":92,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":94,"right":95,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":99,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":99,"left":7,"right":98,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":178,"left":137,"right":177,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":137,"left":121,"right":136,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":110,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":104,"right":109,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":103,"